com.ibm.team.process.common
Interface IIterationConfiguration

public interface IIterationConfiguration

Representation of a configuration of an iteration. Iteration configurations define the process which applies during a particular time interval.

Since:
0.5

Method Summary
 IIterationConfiguration[] getChildIterations()
          Returns the iterations into which this iteration is divided.
 IDevelopmentLineConfiguration getDevelopmentLine()
          Returns the development line configuration within which this iteration configuration has been defined or null if this iteration configuration has been defined in a different context.

          Returns the id of the iteration that this configuration configures or null if no id has been specified.

Method Detail

getId

java.lang.String getId()
Returns the id of the iteration that this configuration configures or null if no id has been specified.

In order for this configuration to be saved to the repository this field must have a non-null value, so it is safe to assume that this method will not return null if it comes from a model built from an immutable item fetched from the repository. It is possible for an incomplete/invalid configuration, however, to return null.

Returns:
the id of this iteration or null

getChildIterations

IIterationConfiguration[] getChildIterations()
Returns the iterations into which this iteration is divided. Returns an empty array if this iteration is undivided.

Returns:
the child iterations or an empty array

getParentIteration

IIterationConfiguration getParentIteration()
Returns the parent iteration of this iteration or null if this iteration does not have a parent.

Returns:
the parent iteration or null

getDevelopmentLine

IDevelopmentLineConfiguration getDevelopmentLine()
Returns the development line configuration within which this iteration configuration has been defined or null if this iteration configuration has been defined in a different context.

Returns:
the development line configuration within which this iteration configuration has been defined or null.
